Object.Field:
This mapping uses traditional insert statement strategies to perform upload operations for a given partition using the IKM Oracle Control Append.
The mapping adds new source data into a given partition, which may already have data in it. Existing data in the partition is preserved during the insert operation.
The Partition/Subpartition property of the target partitioned table has been configured with an ODI variable, PARTITION_MONTH, to set the partition name dynamically (i.e. using an ODI package) and upload data into a given partition.
To test this mapping, perform the following steps:
1. Perform a full load of the partitioned table using any of the packages found under the folder "01 - Initial Load Samples". 2. Delete or truncate MY_STG_AREA.ORDERS table. 3. Add new data into the MY_STG_AREA.ORDERS for a given partition, and run this mapping. You can use the INCREMENTAL.SQL script provided in the sample repository zip file to add additional data for a given partition. 4. Once you add additional data for a given partition, execute this mapping. 5. You should see that the mapping adds the content of the new dataset from the MY_STG_AREA.ORDERS table into the partition of the partitioned table.
This mapping does not update existing data in the partition of the partitioned table. Alternatively, you can use the IKM Oracle Incremental Update to perform update operations and upload data incrementally, but this strategy does not use Oracle Partition Exchange.
